+## 🌙 DreamCatcher-Specific Architecture
+
+### Core Principles
+
+1. **Offline-First Design**: Room is the Single Source of Truth; all UI reads from Room, never directly from Firestore.
+2. **Delta Sync**: Only fetch records where `lastUpdated > localLastSync` to minimize network bandwidth.
+3. **Single Activity Pattern**: One `MainActivity` hosts all Fragments; use Navigation Component for transitions.
+4. **Centralized Threading**: All background work runs on an `ExecutorService` initialized in `MyApplication`.
+5. **Immutable Data Flow**: Repository propagates `LiveData<MutableList<>>` to ViewModels, which observe in Fragments.
+
+### Core Data Models
+
+- **User**: Firestore document at `users/{uid}` — stores profile info, nickname, profile picture URL.
+- **DreamPost**: Room entity + Firestore document — stores dream description, AI-generated image URL, author info, timestamps.
+  - Required fields: `postId`, `authorUid`, `title`, `description`, `imageUrl`, `createdAt`, `lastUpdated`.
+
+### Key Workflows
+
+#### User Registration & Login
+1. Firebase Auth handles email/password validation.
+2. On successful registration, create a Firestore `users/{uid}` document.
+3. On login, retrieve the user document and cache profile info.
+4. Session persists locally via Firebase Auth SDK.
+
+#### Dream Post Creation
+1. User enters dream description in `CreateDreamFragment`.
+2. Call external AI image generation API (DALL·E 3, etc.) — runs off main thread.
+3. Show `LoadingState.LOADING` spinner during API call.
+4. On success, display preview; user adds optional title.
+5. On "Post" tap:
+   - Upload image bitmap to Firebase Storage at `dream_images/{postId}.jpg`.
+   - Create Firestore document in `posts/{postId}` with all metadata.
+   - Insert DreamPost entity into Room database.
+   - Update `LocalSyncManager.setLastUpdated()`.
+
+#### Social Feed
+1. `FeedViewModel` observes `DreamCatcherModel.shared.getAllDreamPosts()` (LiveData from Room).
+2. `FeedFragment` binds LiveData to `FeedAdapter` which renders `DreamPostViewHolder` items.
+3. Pull-to-refresh calls `DreamCatcherModel.shared.refreshPosts()`, which:
+   - Queries Firestore for posts where `lastUpdated > localLastSync`.
+   - Inserts new/updated posts into Room.
+   - Updates sync timestamp in SharedPreferences.
+
+#### My Journal (Offline)
+1. `JournalFragment` filters Room data: `DreamPostDao.getUserDreamPosts(userId)`.
+2. Works entirely offline; no network calls required.
+3. Syncs automatically when user is online.
+
+### Threading Pattern
+
+```kotlin
+// In Application class
+class MyApplication : Application() {
+    val executorService: ExecutorService = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(4)
+    
+    companion object Globals {
+        var appContext: Context? = null
+        var executor: ExecutorService? = null
+    }
+    
+    override fun onCreate() {
+        super.onCreate()
+        appContext = applicationContext
+        executor = executorService
+    }
+}
+
+// In Repository
+fun refreshPosts() {
+    MyApplication.executor?.execute {
+        // Firestore call or DB operation here
+        val posts = firebaseModel.getPosts() // or database.dreamPostDao.getAllPosts()
+        
+        // Post result back to UI thread
+        Handler(Looper.getMainLooper()).post {
+            // Update UI via LiveData
+        }
+    }
+}
+```
+
+### Media Capture Pattern
+
+Always use `ActivityResultContracts` — never `startActivityForResult`:
+
+```kotlin
+// In Fragment
+private val cameraLauncher = registerForActivityResult(ActivityResultContracts.TakePicturePreview()) { bitmap ->
+    bitmap?.let { uploadImage(it) }
+}
+
+private val galleryLauncher = registerForActivityResult(ActivityResultContracts.GetContent()) { uri ->
+    uri?.let { loadImageFromUri(it) }
+}
+
+fun onCameraClicked() {
+    cameraLauncher.launch(null)
+}
+
+fun onGalleryClicked() {
+    galleryLauncher.launch("image/*")
+}
+```
+
+### Advanced Patterns
+
+For detailed information on data synchronization, threading, media capture, and other advanced patterns, see **`rules/ADVANCED_STANDARDS.md`**.
+
